Britain says North Korea H-bomb test would be 'grave breach' of UN resolutions
2016-01-06 07:13:56 GMT
BEIJING: British Foreign Secretary Philip Hammond said on Wednesday a test of a hydrogen nuclear bomb by North Korea would be a "provocation which I condemn without reservation" and a "grave breach" of U.N. Security Council resolutions.Hammond tweeted the statement during his two-day trip to Beijing: "If North Korean H-bomb test reports are true, it is a grave breach of #UNSC resolutions and a provocation which I condemn without reservation."
